# .env.template
#
# Copy to `.env` (no extension change — just remove `.template`) and fill in.
# `.env` is gitignored. NEVER paste a key into chat or commit it.
#
# Format: KEY=value  (no spaces around =, no quotes unless the value contains spaces)
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default ShadowVerse config (manual LLM mode, manual YouTube uploads)
# only requires the two keys in the REQUIRED section below.
# Everything else is optional and only activates a specific automation.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# ===================== REQUIRED =====================

# Pexels — free API, generous limits.
# Get a key: https://www.pexels.com/api/new/  (sign in, click "Get Started")
PEXELS_API_KEY=

# Pixabay — free API, generous limits.
# Get a key: https://pixabay.com/api/docs/  (sign in, scroll to "Your API key")
PIXABAY_API_KEY=

# ===================== OPTIONAL =====================

# ---------- LLM API providers (NOT required in manual mode) ----------
# The pipeline runs in `llm.primary_provider: manual` by default — Claude Code in chat
# sessions handles every LLM call. NEITHER of these keys is needed unless you flip
# `llm.primary_provider` in config.yaml to "anthropic" or "openai" AND add the matching
# package back to requirements.txt.
#
# Anthropic (Claude) — https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
#
# OpenAI (GPT) — https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# ---------- Fact-checking (NOT required in manual mode) ----------
# Same story — manual mode means you (or Claude Code) run the fact-check prompt by hand.
# Activate Perplexity by setting `fact_check.provider: perplexity` in config.yaml.
#
# Perplexity — https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api
# PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=

# ---------- Trend research — YouTube Data API v3 (DEFERRED) ----------
# Activates `trend_pull.pull_youtube_trending()` (Mon competitor data)
# and `analytics_pull.pull_youtube_analytics()` (Sun own-channel metrics).
# Without it, do those steps manually in YouTube Studio (5–10 min each).
# UPLOADS NEVER USE THIS API — uploads are manual via studio.youtube.com forever.
# Setup steps if you ever activate:
#   1. https://console.cloud.google.com/  → create or pick a project
#   2. APIs & Services → Library → enable "YouTube Data API v3"
#   3. APIs & Services → Credentials → Create credentials → API key
#   4. Edit the key → restrict to "YouTube Data API v3" (and ideally an IP range)
# YOUTUBE_API_KEY=

# ---------- Trend research — Reddit (DEFERRED) ----------
# Activates `trend_pull.pull_reddit_top()`. Without it, skip Reddit as a Monday data source.
# Setup if you ever activate:
#   - https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps → "create another app" → type "script"
#   - CLIENT_ID = the short string under the app name (no label; below "personal use script")
#   - CLIENT_SECRET = the longer string labelled "secret"
#   - USER_AGENT format must identify the project (Reddit blocks generic agents)
# REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=
# REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
# REDDIT_USER_AGENT=ShadowVerse/0.1 by official.shadowverse@gmail.com

# ---------- TTS escape hatch (NOT required if F5-TTS local works) ----------
# Activates `tts.provider: elevenlabs` in config.yaml. Only worth it if local F5-TTS
# quality starts hurting retention.
# Get a key: https://elevenlabs.io/app/settings/api-keys
# Free tier ~10 min/mo. Starter $5/mo ~30 min. Creator $22/mo ~100 min.
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# ---------- TikTok auto-upload (Content Posting API) ----------
# Activates tools/tiktok_upload.py — the TikTok sibling of the automated YouTube
# uploader. OFFICIAL API only; cookie auth + 3rd-party uploaders are banned.
# Setup:
#   1. https://developers.tiktok.com/apps → register an app (log in as @shadowversetec's owner)
#   2. Add the "Login Kit" + "Content Posting API" products
#   3. Request scopes: user.info.basic, video.upload (+ video.publish for Phase 2)
#   4. Register a redirect URI (default below) and add privacy-policy + terms URLs
#   5. Move the app to production/Live, then run: python tools/tiktok_oauth_init.py
# NOTE: PUBLIC posting needs the app to pass TikTok's audit; until then posts are
# SELF_ONLY/private. config.yaml tiktok.* controls mode/privacy/enable.
# TIKTOK_CLIENT_KEY=
# TIKTOK_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Optional — only if you registered a non-default redirect URI:
# TIKTOK_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:8742/callback

# ---------- Publishing (Phase 2+) ----------
# Metricool / Buffer / Publer use OAuth, not raw API keys. Add tokens here once you connect
# each platform via their UI. YouTube Shorts uploads stay manual via Studio (do NOT
# automate — see operating guide §14).
# METRICOOL_API_TOKEN=
# BUFFER_API_TOKEN=
